FBIS3-60823 "jptot001__l94071" JPRS-TOT-94-001-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 7 January 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA ISRAEL Hamas Claims Responsibility for Ashdod Guard Murder TA2612114893 Jerusalem THE JERUSALEM POST in English 26 Dec 93 p 1 TA2612114893 Jerusalem THE JERUSALEM POST Language: English Article Type:BFN [Report by ITIM] [Excerpt] A 60-year-old security guard found murdered in Ashdod Thursday evening was apparently the victim of a nationalistic attack, police said last night. Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] claimed responsibility for the murder. Anatoliy Kalsanikov, a guard at a building site in Ashdod's Rova' Tet neighborhood, was found by a night watchman who had come to replace him. Kalsanikov had suffered deep stab wounds in the neck and chest. [passage omitted]
